---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Cellar Consulting" description="Expert guidance on building, curating, and managing a wine collection tailored to your taste and budget.">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-amber-600 font-medium tracking-wider uppercase text-sm mb-3">Services</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-6">Cellar Consulting</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-12 max-w-2xl">
      Whether you're buying your first wine fridge or managing a 500-bottle collection, I help you build a cellar that reflects your palate — and ages gracefully.
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900">Why Work With a Sommelier?</h2>
      <p>Building a wine collection is deceptively complex. Without guidance, most collectors end up with too many bottles from too few regions, wines that peak before they're opened, and gaps where there should be variety. A sommelier brings structure to the process — balancing drinking wines with age-worthy investments, diversifying across regions and styles, and ensuring your collection evolves with your palate.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">What I Offer</h2>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-6">Collection Assessment</h3>
      <p>I review your existing collection (in person or via inventory list), identify strengths and gaps, flag wines approaching their drinking windows, and provide a prioritized "drink now" list. You'll receive a written report with recommendations for future acquisitions that complement what you already own.</p>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-6">Cellar Design & Buildout</h3>
      <p>Starting from scratch? I help you determine the right storage solution for your space and budget — from a 50-bottle wine fridge to a custom-built climate-controlled room. I advise on temperature, humidity, lighting, racking systems, and inventory management tools. I work with local contractors and can recommend trusted vendors for equipment and installation.</p>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-6">Acquisition Strategy</h3>
      <p>Based on your taste profile and budget, I build a purchasing plan that balances:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Daily drinkers</strong> — reliably excellent bottles under $25 for weeknight enjoyment</li>
        <li><strong>Occasion wines</strong> — $40–$100 bottles for dinner parties and celebrations</li>
        <li><strong>Age-worthy investments</strong> — wines with 10–20+ year aging potential from top producers</li>
        <li><strong>Discovery picks</strong> — exciting bottles from emerging regions or under-the-radar producers</li>
      </ul>
      <p>I source through retail, allocation lists, auction houses, and direct-from-winery channels depending on what we're seeking.</p>

      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-6">Ongoing Management</h3>
      <p>For serious collectors, I offer quarterly reviews — checking in on drinking windows, adjusting strategy based on new releases and market conditions, and ensuring your cellar stays balanced as you drink and acquire. Think of it as a financial advisor for your wine portfolio.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">Pricing</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Service</th><th>Details</th><th>Price</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Collection Assessment</td><td>Up to 200 bottles, written report</td><td>$400</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Cellar Design Consultation</td><td>On-site visit, equipment recs, layout plan</td><td>$600</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Acquisition Plan</td><td>Personalized 12-month buying strategy</td><td>$500</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Quarterly Management</td><td>Ongoing review and acquisition support</td><td>$300/quarter</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="text-sm text-stone-500">Wine purchases are separate and billed at cost. I do not take commissions from retailers or distributors.</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10">Storage Conditions Matter</h2>
      <p>Even modest wines benefit from proper storage. Here's what to aim for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Temperature:</strong> 55°F (13°C) — consistent, with minimal fluctuation</li>
        <li><strong>Humidity:</strong> 60–70% — protects corks from drying out</li>
        <li><strong>Light:</strong> Minimal — UV damages wine over time</li>
        <li><strong>Vibration:</strong> None — keep bottles still and horizontal</li>
        <li><strong>Odors:</strong> Wine breathes through the cork; store away from strong-smelling items</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 bg-amber-50 rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
      <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Start building your cellar</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Tell me about your space, budget, and what you love to drink. We'll take it from there.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="bg-amber-600 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium hover:bg-amber-700 transition-colors inline-block">Contact Me</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
